         <div class="caption">
          <h3>
           ‘Surviving R. Kelly’ Producer Dream Hampton Takes On Ecosystem That Supported The Star
          </h3>
          <p>
           <span style="font-family: Georgia, serif; font-size: 17px;">
            Activist, filmmaker and writer dream hampton executive produced
           </span>
           <em style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-family: Georgia, serif; font-size: 17px; line-height: inherit; vertical-align: baseline;">
            Surviving R. Kelly
           </em>
           <span style="font-family: Georgia, serif; font-size: 17px;">
            , a six-part docuseries focusing on Kelly's alleged victims and their family members. hampton says the series, which first premiered on Lifetime on Jan. 3, is currently streaming on
           </span>
           <a href="https://www.mylifetime.com/" style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-family: Georgia, serif; font-size: 17px; line-height: inherit; vertical-align: baseline; color: rgb(80, 118, 184); text-decoration: none;">
            Lifetime's website
           </a>
           <span style="font-family: Georgia, serif; font-size: 17px;">
            and will re-air on Feb. 25, is about "centering the women."
           </span>
          </p>
          <p>
           <a href="https://csrpc.uchicago.edu/feature/surviving_r._kelly_producer_dream_hampton_takes_on_ecosystem_that_supported">
            READ MORE
            <i class="icon-more icon-white">
            </i>
           </a>
          </p>
         </div>
        </div>
