        <h3>
         Hot Topics
        </h3>
        <div id="minifeature">
         <a href="">
         </a>
         <h4>
          Aug 20 | Eve Ewing to Pen Marvel’s “Ironheart” Series
         </h4>
         <p>
          The series will focus on Riri Williams, a black teen girl from Chicago who is a genius and superhero.
          <a href="http://www.chicagotribune.com/entertainment/ct-ent-marvel-ironheart-eve-ewing-0821-story.html">
           Read more here.
          </a>
         </p>
         <a href="">
         </a>
         <h4>
          Aug 8 | Updates on Reconstruction in Puerto Rico
         </h4>
         <p>
          Thousands still left without electricity, while political strife rocks the island territory.
          <a href="https://www.theguardian.com/world/2018/aug/08/puerto-rico-hurricane-maria-electricity-ten-months">
           Read the Guardian series here
          </a>
         </p>
         <a href="">
         </a>
         <h4>
          May 23 | Srikanth Reddy Wins Guggenheim Fellowship
         </h4>
         <p>
          Faculty Affiliate Srikanth Reddy will use the award to complete a new book of poetry, titled “Underworld Lit.”
         </p>
         <a href="">
         </a>
         <h4>
          May 19 | Belew Interviewed by New York Times on White Power
         </h4>
         <p>
          In a
          <a href="https://www.nytimes.com/2018/05/19/us/the-secret-history-of-white-power.html">
           NYT interview
          </a>
          , Faculty Affiliate Kathleen Belew talks about the connections between Vietnam, terrorism, and the White Power movement.
         </p>
